@noinline
def render_svg(d:Diagram, bounds:BoundingBox) -> String =
  (min, max) = bounds
  imgWidth = 400.0
  scaleFactor = imgWidth / (max.x - min.x)
  imgHeight = (max.y - min.y) * scaleFactor
  imgXMin   =  min.x * scaleFactor
  imgYMin   = -max.y * scaleFactor
  AsList(_, objs) = (d | flip_y | scale(scaleFactor)).val
  svgAttrStr = (    "width"   <=> imgWidth
                <+> "height"  <=> imgHeight
                <+> "viewBox" <=> (imgXMin <+> imgYMin <+> imgWidth <+> imgHeight))
  tag_brackets_attr "svg" svgAttrStr $
    concat $ each objs \obj.
      (attr, pos, geom) = obj
      render_geom attr pos geom

def plot_to_diagram(plot:Plot n a b c) -> Diagram given (a:Type, b:Type, c:Type, n|Ix) =
  points = concat_diagrams for i:n.
    x = get_scaled plot.xs i
    y = get_scaled plot.ys i
    c = get_scaled plot.cs i
    # TODO: nested may-fail patterns would make this much better
    case x of
      Just x' -> case y of
        Just y' -> case c of
          Just c' -> point_diagram | move_xy(x', y') | set_stroke_color(color_scale c')
          Nothing -> mempty
        Nothing -> mempty
      Nothing -> mempty
  boundingBox = move_xy(rect 1.0 1.0, 0.5, 0.5)
  boundingBox <> points

contents.rsbText:
def auto_scale(xs:n=>Float) -> ScaledData n Float given (n|Ix) =
  max = maximum xs
  min = minimum xs
  # Add 10% padding away from the plot area
  space = (max - min) * 0.05
  padding = maximum [space, max * 0.001, 0.000001]
  ScaledData (float_scale (min - padding) (max + padding)) xs

def matshow(img:n=>m=>Float) -> Html given (n|Ix, m|Ix) = low = minimum $ flatten2D(img) high = maximum $ flatten2D(img) range = high - low img_to_html $ make_png for i:n j:m. x = if range == 0.0 then float_to_8bit $ 0.5 else float_to_8bit $ (img[i,j] - low) / range [x, x, x]
contents.rsbText:
def matshow(img:n=>m=>Float) -> Html given (n|Ix, m|Ix) =
  low  = minimum $ flatten2D(img)
  high = maximum $ flatten2D(img)
  range = high - low
  img_to_html $ make_png for i:n j:m.
    x = if range == 0.0
      then float_to_8bit $ 0.5
      else float_to_8bit $ (img[i,j] - low) / range
    [x, x, x]
